  "text": "Remark 2.8. For technical reasons (see the proof in [CITATION_1] ), Lemma 2.7 requires that for any r > 0 the function E(r) will satisfy E(r) ≤ min{E(0)/4, 1/4r 2 }. However, we can always assume w.l.o.g. that E satisfies this condition because if it does not, then we can apply Lemma 2.7 with E which is defined as E (r) = min{E(r), E(0)/4, 1/4r 2 }. We will thus disregard this technicality.",
